column5: Happy Thanksgiving all my Walleye Central brothers!
Not Thanksgiving north of the border but nevertheless wish all you americans a great day with family and friends.
Anything similar in your national holidays?
Our Thanksgiving is in early October.......maybe due to earlier harvests in the Great White North......or perhaps our metric calendar.
I would have doubled up this year, but the October 5 snow encouraged me to head home the next day. Travel was tough in the Red Lake area.

Business as usual on this side of the border, but I did eat way to much for lunch yesterday, (in sympathy with the rest of you). I missed the first one too Connie, as well as the opener of moose season.
